def nt(n): prime = [True] * (n + 1) p = 2 for p in range(2, int(n**0.5) + 1): if prime[p]: for i in range(p * p, n + 1, p): prime[i] = False return [p for p in range(2, n + 1) if prime[p]] def tong(n): s = 0 while n > 0: s += n % 10 n //= 10 return s primes = nt(10000000) m,n = map(int,input().split()) for i in range(m,n+1): if tong(i) in primes: print(i) break else: print(-1)
